# stphtoolbox
This R package Swiss TPH toolbox for reproducible research

It aims to contain useful:
- templates
- graphic representation based on `ggplot2`

## About
This package was developed on a Windows 10 x64 (build 19045) operating system, with R version 4.3.2 (2023-10-31 ucrt), RStudio version 2023.09.1 Build 494 and Rtools43.
For Windows users, it is smoother to install 1) Rtools, 2) R and 3) RStudio in this order.

### Installation from GitHub
To install the `stphtoolbox` package on your workstation, you can
- either download the `master` branch as a ZIP and build the package locally
- or install the latest released version (preferred option) 

```r
library(devtools)
devtools::install_github("Research-IT-Swiss-TPH/stphtoolbox")
```

An index of available documentation for the `stphtoolbox` is displayed using the `help()` function

```r
help(package="stphtoolbox")
```
